# Rating

Star rating control for feedback input. It supports half-star precision, read-only display, custom colors, custom icons, sizing, and click animation.

## Basic Usage

### Half-star Rating

Use `precision="0.5"` for half-step ratings. Half stars fill from the left side.

::TuffDemoWrapper{demo="RatingBasicDemo" code-lang="vue"}
---
code: |
  <script setup lang="ts">
  import { ref } from 'vue'

  const score = ref(3.5)
  </script>

  <template>
    <TxRating v-model="score" :precision="0.5" show-text />
  </template>
---
::

## Style Customization

Use `filled-color`, `empty-color`, `hover-color`, `text-color`, `size`, and `gap` to tune the visual style. The demo includes orange, green read-only, and compact violet appearances.

::TuffDemoWrapper{demo="RatingStyleDemo" code-lang="vue"}
---
code: |
  <script setup lang="ts">
  import { ref } from 'vue'

  const score = ref(4)
  </script>

  <template>
    <TxRating
      v-model="score"
      :size="28"
      :gap="6"
      :precision="0.5"
      filled-color="#f97316"
      empty-color="rgba(148, 163, 184, 0.34)"
      hover-color="#fb923c"
      text-color="var(--tx-color-warning)"
      show-text
    />
  </template>
---
::

## Custom Icons

Set `icon` to reuse one icon for all states, or use `filled-icon`, `empty-icon`, and `half-icon` separately. Built-in icons, Iconify classes, and emoji are supported, including hearts, diamonds, and face icons.

::TuffDemoWrapper{demo="RatingIconDemo" code-lang="vue"}
---
code: |
  <script setup lang="ts">
  import { ref } from 'vue'

  const mood = ref(3)
  const hearts = ref(4.5)
  </script>

  <template>
    <TxRating v-model="mood" icon="💎" :size="26" filled-color="#38bdf8" show-text />
    <TxRating
      v-model="hearts"
      :precision="0.5"
      :size="28"
      icon="i-carbon-favorite-filled"
      filled-color="#f43f5e"
      empty-color="rgba(244, 63, 94, 0.18)"
      show-text
    />
  </template>
---
::

## Click Animation

Rating plays a more visible bounce + glow + ripple animation after a click by default. Set `:animated="false"` to disable it.

::TuffDemoWrapper{demo="RatingAnimationDemo" code-lang="vue"}
---
code: |
  <script setup lang="ts">
  import { ref } from 'vue'

  const animated = ref(2)
  const still = ref(2)
  </script>

  <template>
    <TxRating v-model="animated" :precision="0.5" show-text />
    <TxRating v-model="still" :animated="false" filled-color="#a78bfa" show-text />
  </template>
---
::

## Interaction Contract

Rating exposes the star group as a radio group. `disabled` and `readonly` both block updates; `readonly` is display-only and removes star button interaction while keeping the rating visible.

## API

### Props
::TuffPropsTable
---
rows:
  - name: modelValue
    type: number
    default: '0'
    description: Current score passed by `v-model`.
  - name: maxStars
    type: number
    default: '5'
    description: Number of rendered star buttons.
  - name: precision
    type: "number | 0.5"
    default: '1'
    description: Step size. `0.5` enables half-star toggling; other numeric values only affect score text precision.
  - name: showText
    type: boolean
    default: 'false'
    description: Show score text
  - name: disabled
    type: boolean
    default: 'false'
    description: Disables star buttons and marks the root as aria-disabled.
  - name: readonly
    type: boolean
    default: 'false'
    description: Display-only mode. Star buttons are disabled and the root is marked aria-readonly.
  - name: icon
    type: "string | TxIconSource"
    default: '-'
    description: Shared icon used by filled and empty layers when state-specific icons are not provided.
  - name: filledIcon
    type: "string | TxIconSource"
    default: 'star'
    description: Filled icon. Falls back to `icon`, then `star`.
  - name: emptyIcon
    type: "string | TxIconSource"
    default: 'star'
    description: Empty icon. Falls back to `icon`, then `star`.
  - name: halfIcon
    type: "string | TxIconSource"
    default: '-'
    description: Half icon. When omitted, Rating clips the filled layer from the left.
  - name: filledColor
    type: string
    default: '#fbbf24'
    description: Filled icon color; CSS fallback is `#fbbf24`.
  - name: emptyColor
    type: string
    default: '#d1d5db'
    description: Empty icon color; CSS fallback is `#d1d5db`.
  - name: hoverColor
    type: string
    default: 'filledColor'
    description: Hover color for the filled layer; falls back to `filledColor` / `#fbbf24`.
  - name: textColor
    type: string
    default: '#6b7280'
    description: Score text color; CSS fallback is `#6b7280`.
  - name: size
    type: "number | string"
    default: '20px'
    description: Star icon size. Numbers are converted to px; CSS fallback is `20px`.
  - name: gap
    type: "number | string"
    default: '2px'
    description: Gap between stars. Numbers are converted to px; CSS fallback is `2px`.
  - name: animated
    type: boolean
    default: 'true'
    description: Play the click pop / ripple animation after selection.
---
:::

### Events

| Event | Payload | Description |
|-------|---------|-------------|
| `update:modelValue` | `(value: number)` | Emitted after an interactive star click with the next rating value. |
| `change` | `(value: number)` | Mirrors `update:modelValue` for consumers that use change handlers. |

### Slots

| Slot | Props | Description |
|------|-------|-------------|
| `text` | `{ value: number, max: number }` | Replaces the default `value / max` label when `showText` is true. |

## Best Practices

- Use `precision="0.5"` only when half-step feedback is meaningful. For yes/no confidence or coarse satisfaction, full stars are easier to scan.
- Keep `disabled` for unavailable input and `readonly` for display-only historical scores; both block updates, but they communicate different intent.
- Provide `showText` or a custom `#text` slot when exact numeric value matters, especially for half-star values.
- Prefer state-specific `filledIcon` / `emptyIcon` / `halfIcon` only when the icon set has clear contrast. Otherwise use one shared `icon` and tune colors.
- Disable `animated` in dense forms, tables, or reduced-motion-heavy contexts where click pop animation distracts from the data entry flow.

## Review Notes

- Reviewed against `packages/tuffex/packages/components/src/rating/src/types.ts`, `TxRating.vue`, and `rating.test.ts`.
- Existing tests cover half-star clipping, full-star and half-star reselection, model/change emission, readonly/disabled blocking, custom colors/icons/sizing, disabled animation, radio semantics, and `text` slot props.
- API note: `precision="0.5"` enables half-star toggling when clicking the currently selected full star; other numeric precision values affect score text precision only.
- Accessibility note: the star row is a radio group. Use `readonly` for historical display and `disabled` for unavailable input.

